file.name: schema.yml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  title: LORIS - REST API endpoints
  description: The LORIS API uses standard HTTP error codes and the body of any response will either be empty or contain only a JSON object for any request.
  contact:
    name: LORIS Development Team
    url: 'https://github.com/aces/loris'
  license:
    name: 'GNU Public License, Version 3'
    url: 'https://opensource.org/licenses/GPL-3.0'
  version: 0.0.3
servers:
  - url: /
security:
  - ApiKeyAuth: []
paths:
  '/candidate_list':
    get:
      tags:
        - Candidates
      parameters:
        - name: format
          in: query
          required: false
          schema:
            type: string

      responses:
        '200':
          description: The module HTML page
          content:
            text/html:
              schema:
                type: string
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/MenuFilterData'
  '/candidate_list/validateIDs':
    get:
      tags:
        - Candidates
      parameters:
        - name: CandID
          in: query
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string 
        - name: PSCID
          in: query
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string 
      responses:
        '200':
          description: The string 1 if the candidate exists, 0 otherwise
          content:
            text/plain:
              schema:
                type: string
              example: '1'
components:
  schemas:
    MenuFilterData:
      type: object
      properties:
        Data:
          type: array
          items:
            $ref: '#/components/schemas/MenuFilterRow'
        fieldOptions:
          type: object
          additionalProperties:
            type: object
            additionalProperties:
              type: string
    MenuFilterRow:
      type: array
      items:
        type: string
  securitySchemes:
    ApiKeyAuth:
      type: apiKey
      name: Authorization
      in: header
